    "client_msg_id": "8880d368-1671-46a8-b95e-9bbe524f915f",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Great question.\n\nI am planning to have cycles (not quite there yet). But I'm going to try to do something to statically guarantee that the cycles break after a bounded time, or else it'll be considered an invalid graph configuration.\n\nI'm only giving myself about 3ms per frame to do all calculations, so I need to be careful about variability in potential frame times. I don't want a pathological case blowing my time budget, even if that means (eg) constraining the model such that it's not Turing complete.",
    "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "ts": "1535833114.000100",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
